Type Parameters
Name Description
T
Remarks
Values are kept in order in which they are added. Order can be modified by MoveFirst(T), MoveLast(T), MoveBefore(T, T), MoveAfter(T, T).

TrimExcess()

Sets the capacity of this list to the size of the list (rounded up to nearest prime), unless count is 0, in which case we release references. This method can be used to minimize a list's memory overhead once it is known that no new elements will be added to the list. To completely clear a list and release all memory referenced by the list, execute the following statements: Clear(); TrimExcess();

public void TrimExcess()

UnionWith(IEnumerable<T>)

Take the union of this HashSet with other. Modifies this set. Implementation note: GetSuggestedCapacity (to increase capacity in advance avoiding multiple resizes ended up not being useful in practice; quickly gets to the point where it's a wasteful check.
